 A mystical 8-Ball proclaimed its reply;
Its wisdom was profound, it said, "Signs point to yes."
With this magical answer, we must all be thankful;
For every choice we make, these signs will help us rank 'em.
In this world of chance, our actions can only progress.

 A new horizon awaits;
Embrace each moment, it shines;
Outlook, forever good.

 Echoing a gentle 'yes,'
Mind opens like blossoming lotus;
Heart dances to its tune.

 Wisdom's veil keeps some secrets safe;
Share not all you know, for now;
Time unfolds, answers may come.

 Clouds gather, the sun fades away,
Don't count on a rainbow today;
Stillness can bring hidden wonders.

 Dark clouds loom overhead,
Raining on parade of joy;
Outlook may not be so good.

 Dark clouds gather 'round,
Soon to drench our parched earth;
Umbrella, prepare for storm.

 Clouds hide sun, confusion reigns supreme;
Truth's mirror fractured, reflection unseen.
Decisions, oh decisions, uncertain fate.
